sor Docs](https://cursor.com/docs/subagents)\n\nCreate specialized AI subagents for task-specific workflows and context management.\n\n**02. Cloud Agents `https://cursor.com/docs/cloud-agent`**\n\n`https://cursor.com/docs/cloud-agent`\n![](https://us1.discourse-cdn.com/cursor1/original/3X/9/d/9d8f2e2c1ddc1aa36ec403e867ad2a77efa6256c.png)\n![](https://us1.discourse-cdn.com/cursor1/optimized/3X/8/0/803aef7ed977566553b9753a462ef9e1dc1aa980_2_690x362.png)\n\n### [Cloud Agents | Cursor Docs](https://cursor.com/docs/cloud-agent)\n\nRun Agent in the cloud for continuous coding assistance.\n\n**03. Automations** `https://cursor.com/docs/cloud-agent/automations`\n\n`https://cursor.com/docs/cloud-agent/automations`\n![](https://us1.discourse-cdn.com/cursor1/original/3X/9/d/9d8f2e2c1ddc1aa36ec403e867ad2a77efa6256c.png)\n![](https://us1.discourse-cdn.com/cursor1/optimized/3X/c/a/caa51218f9bc2a042b0bf88d5b31592450a621a2_2_690x362.png)\n\n### [Automations | Cursor Docs](https://cursor.com/docs/cloud-agent/automations)\n\nRun cloud agents automatically on a schedule or in response to events.\n\n**04. “Multitask” mode**\n\nI can’t find docs for ‘Multitask’ mode (accessible at bottom of prompt UI) on `https://cursor.com/docs`.\n\n`https://cursor.com/docs`\n\n**05. And some possibly related articles:**\n\n`https://cursor.com/help/ai-features/multi-agent`\n![](https://us1.discourse-cdn.com/cursor1/original/3X/9/d/9d8f2e2c1ddc1aa36ec403e867ad2a77efa6256c.png)\n![](https://us1.discourse-cdn.com/cursor1/optimized/3X/6/8/686f7b17ac6946164022bc5894f24f3f4bc2287b_2_690x362.png)\n\n### [What is multi-agent coding? | Cursor Docs](https://cursor.com/help/ai-features/multi-agent)\n\nMulti-agent coding runs several AI agents in parallel on different tasks. Learn how to run, multitask, and manage multiple agents in Cursor.\n\n-`https://cursor.com/blog/self-driving-codebases`\n\n`https://cursor.com/blog/self-driving-codebases`\n![](https://us1.discourse-cdn.com/cursor1/original/3X/3/6/364b618c053b00d0a4374462e1bf61a69bf8783b.png)\n![](https://us1.discourse-cdn.com/cursor1/optimized/3X/6/8/681b6d6f2c7ad60752af9f2cc757a47c6ab09ce6_2_690x362.png)\n\n### [Towards self-driving codebases · Cursor](https://cursor.com/blog/self-driving-codebases)\n\nWe're making a part of our multi-agent research harness available to try today in preview.\n\nApologies if any or all of the above concepts are not related to your question.\n\nUnfortunately, I don’t yet know the relationship or difference between all of the concepts above, and in what scenarios you would use each one.\n\nMaybe someone else here does ![:slight_smile:](https://emoji.discourse-cdn.com/fluentui/slight_smile.png?v=15 \":slight_smile:\") .\n\n![:slight_smile:](https://emoji.discourse-cdn.com/fluentui/slight_smile.png?v=15 \":slight_smile:\")\n\nA Google Search prompt I just tried was:\n\nBased on your understanding of `[https://cursor.com/docs/subagents\\`](https://cursor.com/docs/subagents%5C%60), `[https://cursor.com/docs/cloud-agent\\`](https://cursor.com/docs/cloud-agent%5C%60), `[https://cursor.com/docs/cloud-agent/automations\\`](https://cursor.com/docs/cloud-agent/automations%5C%60), `[https://cursor.com/help/ai-features/multi-agent\\`](https://cursor.com/help/ai-features/multi-agent%5C%60) and `[https://cursor.com/blog/self-driving-codebases\\`](https://cursor.com/blog/self-driving-codebases%5C%60), what is the relationship or difference between all of the concepts above (Subagents, Cloud Agents, Automations), and in what scenarios you would use each one.\n\nIts kind of taking these concepts one step forward (or going a step higher).\n\n### Related topics\n\n| Topic |  | Replies | Views | Activity |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| [Cursor subagents are… kinda insane](https://forum.cursor.com/t/cursor-subagents-are-kinda-insane/152030)  [Built for Cursor](/c/showcase/built-for-cursor/19) [rules](https://forum.cursor.com/tag/rules/295) ,  [subagents](https://forum.cursor.com/tag/subagents/348) | 5 |